, \"from\": 899, \"to\": 909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Levels ofE colibacteria in the Seine are being monitored by stressed organisers and frazzled scientists on a constant basis, and over the past few weeks those readings have been on a hygiene knife-edge.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.115357665049746e-17, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Levels\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"ofE colibacteria\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"stressed organisers\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"scientists\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"a constant basis\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"the past few weeks\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"those readings\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"a hygiene knife-edge\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1134}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The river is meant to host open water swimming and triathlon events next week, but heavy downpours could tip readings back towards unsafe territory, as they have been for most of the year.\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The river\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"open water swimming and triathlon events\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy downpours\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"readings\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1253}, {\"ngram\": \"unsafe territory\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1283}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is no wonder the Paris mayor,Anne Hidalgo, put off last week'sswimming stuntfor as long as she possibly could.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1357, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no wonder\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is confidence among organisers that the dry mid-July weather has done enough to lower pollution levels and avoid the drastic option of cancelling the swimming leg and turningthe triathlon into a duathlon, but it is just one of a number of issues that have weighed on them in the build-up to these Games.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"the dry mid-July weather\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution levels\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"the drastic option\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming leg\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"turningthe triathlon\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"a duathlon\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1681}, {\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"the build-up\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chief among them is security.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chief\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheseOlympicscome less than a decade after the deadliest terrorist incident in French history, the 2015 attacks on the Bataclan and other sites around Paris, which left deep scars and a city on edge.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1860, \"end\": 1874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0718371800400905e-60, \"text\": \"Bataclan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\"}, {\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the deadliest terrorist incident\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1856}, {\"ngram\": \"deep scars\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"edge\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This reporter was in a fan park by the Eiffel Tower at Euro 2016 when a popping noise sparked a terrifying stampede to escape what was presumed to be the sound of a gun.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This reporter\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"a fan park\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2032}, {\"ngram\": \"Euro\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2040}, {\"ngram\": \"a popping noise\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2066}, {\"ngram\": \"a terrifying stampede\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2096}, {\"ngram\": \"the sound\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"a gun\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It turned out to be firecrackers, but people assumed the worst.\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2214, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"firecrackers\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games arrive at a time of tension in France following the snap election earlier this month, which sawviolence break outon the streets after a shock win for the country's left-wing coalition blocked the far-right from taking power.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1948_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0541361255215584e-36, \"text\": \"The Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1948_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1948_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998971702975612, \"rank\": 9.264743673941713e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2242}, {\"ngram\": \"tension\", \"from\": 2246, \"to\": 2253}, {\"ngram\": \"the snap election\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"which sawviolence break outon\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2341}, {\"ngram\": \"a shock win\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2371}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's left-wing coalition\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"the far-right\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Protesters could be seen launching flares, setting e-bikes on fire and clashing with police.\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Protesters\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"flares\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2492}, {\"ngram\": \"e\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2503}, {\"ngram\": \"bikes\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2509}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2517}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Security is at the heart of everything we do,\\\"Paris 2024CEOEtienne Thobois toldThe Independentearlier this year.\", \"from\": 2545, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Security\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2554}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2570}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2584}, {\"ngram\": \"Thobois toldThe Independentearlier\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a huge plan being put in place.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a huge plan\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tens of thousands of people are going to be implemented and not one stone has been left unturned.\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tens of thousands\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2718}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2728}, {\"ngram\": \"not one stone\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not about being confident, it is about being thorough, and to limit the risks that will always remain.\\\"\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2908, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the risks\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are also concerns around temperatures whichare expected to soar beyond 30Cnext week, making all manner of events a serious health risk.\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"temperatures\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2953}, {\"ngram\": \"30Cnext week\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"all manner\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3018}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Olympic Village, accommodation was built without air conditioning in order to boost the Games' environmental credentials, but organisers U-turned after a backlash from national associations, and a supply of 2,500 temporary units will now serve the 7,000 rooms on site.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Village\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3074}, {\"ngram\": \"accommodation\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3089}, {\"ngram\": \"air conditioning\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3124}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 3128, \"to\": 3133}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' environmental credentials\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3195}, {\"ngram\": \"U\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3197}, {\"ngram\": \"a backlash\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3221}, {\"ngram\": \"national associations\", \"from\": 3227, \"to\": 3248}, {\"ngram\": \"a supply\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3262}, {\"ngram\": \"2,500 temporary units\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3287}, {\"ngram\": \"the 7,000 rooms\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3318}, {\"ngram\": \"site\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That response has not satisfied everyone.\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That response\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3342}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sleep is increasingly considered critical to elite performance and some of the wealthier nations, including Britain, Australia and the USA, are bringing, buying or renting their own air-conditioning units.\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3479, \"end\": 3486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999986801630781, \"rank\": 1.3186801384074482e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3488, \"end\": 3497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999994522862373, \"rank\": 5.477154926004482e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.086898345144313e-13, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sleep\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3376}, {\"ngram\": \"elite performance\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3433}, {\"ngram\": \"the wealthier nations\", \"from\": 3446, \"to\": 3467}, {\"ngram\": \"their own air-conditioning units\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We appreciate the concept of not having air conditioning due to the carbon footprint,\\\" Australian Olympic chief Matt Carroll said.\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3665, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9530783966620867, \"rank\": 0.03719628623693421, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 3690, \"end\": 3702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Carroll_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9257385252731692, \"rank\": 0.05365853658533906, \"text\": \"Matt Carroll\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Carroll_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Carroll_(basketball)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3603}, {\"ngram\": \"air conditioning\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3634}, {\"ngram\": \"the carbon footprint\", \"from\": 3642, \"to\": 3662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it is a high-performance Games.\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3745, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a high-performance Games\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are not going for a picnic.\\\"\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a picnic\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3775}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosting the Olympics is always a show of soft power to the world, and so Paris is attempting to present itself in a certain light while hiding some raw realities.\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3852, \"end\": 3857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3799}, {\"ngram\": \"a show\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3816}, {\"ngram\": \"soft power\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3830}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3843}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain light\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3908}, {\"ngram\": \"some raw realities\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 3940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of those is rats: the city has undergone a mass purge using mechanical traps and chemicals, and shutting off sewer exit points, led by expert exterminators called the Smash Team.\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 4124, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rats\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 3962}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 3972}, {\"ngram\": \"a mass purge\", \"from\": 3987, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"mechanical traps\", \"from\": 4006, \"to\": 4022}, {\"ngram\": \"chemicals\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4036}, {\"ngram\": \"sewer exit points\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4072}, {\"ngram\": \"expert exterminators\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4101}, {\"ngram\": \"the Smash Team\", \"from\": 4109, \"to\": 4123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a dark parallel, city officials have been accused of social cleansing after police broke up migrant camps earlier this month and homeless people were systematically removed from the capital's streets.\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a dark parallel\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4144}, {\"ngram\": \"city officials\", \"from\": 4146, \"to\": 4160}, {\"ngram\": \"social cleansing\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4198}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4211}, {\"ngram\": \"migrant camps\", \"from\": 4221, \"to\": 4234}, {\"ngram\": \"homeless people\", \"from\": 4258, \"to\": 4273}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's streets\", \"from\": 4307, \"to\": 4328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since April 2023, almost 13,000 people on the margins of Paris - largely immigrants, people sleeping rough and sex workers - have been removed, according to a report by a group of human rights organisations and charities calledLe Revers de la Medaille(the other side of the medal).\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4387, \"end\": 4392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 4336, \"to\": 4341}, {\"ngram\": \"almost 13,000 people\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4368}, {\"ngram\": \"the margins\", \"from\": 4372, \"to\": 4383}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4421}, {\"ngram\": \"rough and sex workers\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4452}, {\"ngram\": \"a report\", \"from\": 4487, \"to\": 4495}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4506}, {\"ngram\": \"human rights organisations\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"charities\", \"from\": 4541, \"to\": 4550}, {\"ngram\": \"Revers de la\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4572}, {\"ngram\": \"Medaille(the other side\", \"from\": 4573, \"to\": 4596}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4609}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While government and city officials have been tasked with presenting the best of Paris, the organising committee's primary task of delivering the Games has been relatively straightforward, given how much of the sporting infrastructure was already in place and how little had to be built from scratch.\", \"from\": 4613, \"to\": 4913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4694, \"end\": 4699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"government and city officials\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4648}, {\"ngram\": \"the organising committee's primary task\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4740}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4764}, {\"ngram\": \"the sporting infrastructure\", \"from\": 4820, \"to\": 4847}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 4868}, {\"ngram\": \"scratch\", \"from\": 4905, \"to\": 4912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only major new venue is the Aquatics Centre, though that comes with the bizarre catch that it will not host a single swimming race, despite promises that it would in the city's original bid.\", \"from\": 4914, \"to\": 5108, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The only major new venue\", \"from\": 4914, \"to\": 4938}, {\"ngram\": \"the Aquatics Centre\", \"from\": 4942, \"to\": 4961}, {\"ngram\": \"the bizarre catch\", \"from\": 4986, \"to\": 5003}, {\"ngram\": \"a single swimming race\", \"from\": 5026, \"to\": 5048}, {\"ngram\": \"promises\", \"from\": 5058, \"to\": 5066}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's original bid\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fina, swimming's global governing body, demands a venue capacity of at least 15,000 seats for major events like the Olympic Games, but Paris's shiny new \\u20ac175m (\\u00a3147m) Aquatics Centre will host only artistic swimming, diving and water polo in front of 5,000 fans, while the far bigger La Defense Arena will now put on the swimming.It has been reportedthat the reduction in capacity was decided as the venue's budget spiralled from its original \\u20ac70m, though a spokesman for the Paris 2024 organising committee denied this toThe Independent, insisting the decision was purely logistical.\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5245, \"end\": 5250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.685603767368519e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5394, \"end\": 5404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Defense\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\"}, {\"begin\": 5586, \"end\": 5596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5944998233608687e-33, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5636, \"end\": 5647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.031891769713505e-23, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fina\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5114}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming's global governing body\", \"from\": 5116, \"to\": 5148}, {\"ngram\": \"a venue capacity\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5174}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 15,000 seats\", \"from\": 5178, \"to\": 5199}, {\"ngram\": \"major events\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5216}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 5222, \"to\": 5239}, {\"ngram\": \"only artistic swimming, diving and water polo\", \"from\": 5303, \"to\": 5348}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 5352, \"to\": 5357}, {\"ngram\": \"5,000 fans\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5371}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming\", \"from\": 5427, \"to\": 5439}, {\"ngram\": \"reportedthat\", \"from\": 5452, \"to\": 5464}, {\"ngram\": \"the reduction\", \"from\": 5465, \"to\": 5478}, {\"ngram\": \"capacity\", \"from\": 5482, \"to\": 5490}, {\"ngram\": \"the venue's budget\", \"from\": 5506, \"to\": 5524}, {\"ngram\": \"a spokesman\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5577}, {\"ngram\": \"organising committee\", \"from\": 5597, \"to\": 5617}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 5659, \"to\": 5671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is worth pointing out that a corruption probe still hangs over the organising committee, after French police raided the house of CEO Thobois and seized documents as part of synchronised raids on the Olympics' headquarters and the offices of companies awarded contracts to help deliver the Games.\", \"from\": 5696, \"to\": 5994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5794, \"end\": 5807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.542309990276747e-54, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a corruption probe\", \"from\": 5726, \"to\": 5744}, {\"ngram\": \"the organising committee\", \"from\": 5762, \"to\": 5786}, {\"ngram\": \"the house\", \"from\": 5815, \"to\": 5824}, {\"ngram\": \"CEO Thobois\", \"from\": 5828, \"to\": 5839}, {\"ngram\": \"documents\", \"from\": 5851, \"to\": 5860}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 5864, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"synchronised raids\", \"from\": 5872, \"to\": 5890}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics' headquarters\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 5920}, {\"ngram\": \"the offices\", \"from\": 5925, \"to\": 5936}, {\"ngram\": \"companies\", \"from\": 5940, \"to\": 5949}, {\"ngram\": \"contracts\", \"from\": 5958, \"to\": 5967}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 5984, \"to\": 5993}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The investigation into \\\"illegal conflict of interest, misuse of public funds and favouritism\\\" remains ongoing, and no charges have been brought against anyone involved.\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6163, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The investigation\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6012}, {\"ngram\": \"illegal conflict\", \"from\": 6019, \"to\": 6035}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 6039, \"to\": 6047}, {\"ngram\": \"misuse\", \"from\": 6049, \"to\": 6055}, {\"ngram\": \"public funds\", \"from\": 6059, \"to\": 6071}, {\"ngram\": \"favouritism\", \"from\": 6076, \"to\": 6087}, {\"ngram\": \"no charges\", \"from\": 6110, \"to\": 6120}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 6147, \"to\": 6153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thobois toldThe Independenthe was shocked by the raids but added that \\\"it's part of the job\\\".\", \"from\": 6164, \"to\": 6257, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thobois toldThe Independenthe\", \"from\": 6164, \"to\": 6193}, {\"ngram\": \"the raids\", \"from\": 6209, \"to\": 6218}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 6240, \"to\": 6244}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 6248, \"to\": 6255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of which means organisers and city officials cannot wait for the Games to get into full swing, and for the stars to take the stage.\", \"from\": 6259, \"to\": 6394, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6288}, {\"ngram\": \"city officials\", \"from\": 6293, \"to\": 6307}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6324, \"to\": 6333}, {\"ngram\": \"full swing\", \"from\": 6346, \"to\": 6356}, {\"ngram\": \"the stars\", \"from\": 6366, \"to\": 6375}, {\"ngram\": \"the stage\", \"from\": 6384, \"to\": 6393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be a year when mental health is in the spotlight, asSimone Biles returnsto perform under intense scrutiny following her struggles in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6539, \"end\": 6544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999939457249193, \"rank\": 6.054236956352094e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a year\", \"from\": 6409, \"to\": 6415}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health\", \"from\": 6421, \"to\": 6434}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 6441, \"to\": 6454}, {\"ngram\": \"asSimone Biles returnsto\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6480}, {\"ngram\": \"intense scrutiny\", \"from\": 6495, \"to\": 6511}, {\"ngram\": \"her struggles\", \"from\": 6522, \"to\": 6535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty and Caeleb Dressel, two of the pool's alpha swimmers, will compete after having taken time away to look after their mental wellbeing.\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6546, \"end\": 6556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 6561, \"end\": 6575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pool's alpha swimmers\", \"from\": 6584, \"to\": 6609}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 6643, \"to\": 6647}, {\"ngram\": \"their mental wellbeing\", \"from\": 6667, \"to\": 6689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their stories can be inspirational both in glory and in defeat.\", \"from\": 6691, \"to\": 6754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their stories\", \"from\": 6691, \"to\": 6704}, {\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 6734, \"to\": 6739}, {\"ngram\": \"defeat\", \"from\": 6747, \"to\": 6753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are many potential headline acts, like the American sprinter Noah Lyles, the Canadian teenage swimming sensation Summer McIntosh and French judo king Teddy Riner.\", \"from\": 6756, \"to\": 6924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6805, \"end\": 6813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4803366233870595e-15, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6823, \"end\": 6833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\